REVIEWER NOTE: This PR is stacked on https://github.com/angular/angular/pull/68517.

This enables the use of the `experimentalWebMcpTool` option on signal forms and implicitly declares a WebMCP tool based on the form data model. This is an experiment inspirted by the WebMCP declarative forms API to see \
if Angular's framework-level knowledge of the form's declarative data model can produce higher quality WebMCP tools than the web standard can on its own with less effort from the developer.

Example:

```typescript
// main.ts

import {bootstrapApplication} from '@angular/platform-browser';
import {provideExperimentalWebMcpForms} from '@angular/forms';
import {MyComp} from './form';

bootstrapApplication(MyComp, {
  providers: [
    // Activate the feature.
    provideExperimentalWebMcpForms(),
  ],
});
```

```typescript
// form.ts

import {Component, signal} from '@angular/core';
import {form} from '@angular/forms';

@Component({ /* ... */ })
export class MyComp {
  private readonly f = form(signal({
    firstName: '',
    lastName: '',
  }), {
    // Implicitly creates a WebMCP tool named `createUser` which accepts a `firstName` and `lastName` as parameters.
    experimentalWebMcpTool: {
      name: 'createUser',
      description: 'Creates a user with the given name.',
    },

    // Invokes the submit action when the agent calls the WebMCP tool.
    submission: {
      action: () => {
        console.log('User clicked submit, or agent called the tool!');
      },
    },
  });

  // ...
}
```

/cc @alan-agius4 @JeanMeche

### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

Modern Angular (zoneless with signal) has really good performance compared to React, but there is one scenario where it is terribly slow, see `swapRows`:

<img width="254" height="716" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c5fb0f62-f555-4330-9cb7-195aae5cfeea" />
https://krausest.github.io/js-framework-benchmark/2026/chrome146_2.html

### Angular swapRows
https://github.com/krausest/js-framework-benchmark/blob/master/frameworks/keyed/angular-cf-signals-nozone/src/app/app.component.ts#L120
```ts
    const tmp = this.data();
    if (tmp.length > 998) {
      const a = tmp[1];
      tmp[1] = tmp[998];
      tmp[998] = a;
      this.data.set(tmp);
    }
```

### React swapRows
https://github.com/krausest/js-framework-benchmark/blob/master/frameworks/keyed/react-classes/src/main.jsx#L144
```ts
  if (data.length > 998) {
    const newdata = [...data];
    const d1 = newdata[1];
    const d998 = newdata[998];
    newdata[1] = d998;
    newdata[998] = d1;
    return this.setState({ data: newdata });
  }
```

---

The implementations are very close, the only difference is that Angular reads the data from the signal. Is reading the data from the signal may be the reason for this slowness?


